This was the roth (Legio X), afterwards so distinguished for fidelity and courage. As soon as the Helvetians set out through the territory of the Sequani, Caesar hastened to Hither Gaul, enrolled two new legions (XI and ΧΗ), and called from their winter quarters the three (VII, VIII and IX) that were stationed in that province (see Chap. rol).
